<p>95% of all web pages have zero backlinks. The pages that rank on the first page of Google have 3.8x more backlinks than everyone else.</p>
<p>The difference between page 1 and page 50 often comes down to do-follow backlink sites. These are the websites that pass link equity directly to your domain, telling Google your content deserves to rank.</p>
<p>We compiled 203 do-follow backlink sites across 15 categories. Every site on this list passes dofollow links, is active in 2026, and includes the domain authority estimate so you can prioritize. We organized them by type: profile creation, guest posting, forums, social bookmarking, Web 2.0, document sharing, image sharing, video sharing, Q&amp;A platforms, .EDU sites, .GOV sites, and more.</p>
<p>Here is what this list covers:</p>
<ul>
<li>35 high DA profile creation sites with dofollow links</li>
<li>25 guest posting sites that accept contributor articles</li>
<li>20 forum posting sites with dofollow signatures and posts</li>
<li>18 social bookmarking sites with dofollow links</li>
