<td>Must be explicitly added</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Google behavior</td>
<td>Crawls and follows</td>
<td>May or may not follow</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table></div>
<p>Both link types matter for a healthy backlink profile. But dofollow links carry the direct ranking power that moves pages up in search results.</p>
<h2>Why Do-Follow Backlinks Still Matter in 2026</h2>
<p>Backlinks remain a top 3 ranking factor according to Google. Here is the data.</p>
<ul>
<li>Pages in the top 10 Google results have <strong>3.8x more backlinks</strong> than lower-ranking pages.</li>
<li>Websites with strong <a href="/blog/backlink-statistics/">backlink profiles</a> receive <strong>67% more organic traffic</strong> than competitors.</li>
<li><strong>89.2% of SEOs</strong> report ranking improvements within 1-6 months of building quality backlinks.</li>
<li>The #1 ranking page earns an additional <strong>5-14.5% more dofollow backlinks</strong> from new websites each month.</li>
</ul>
<p>The key distinction: quality over quantity. One dofollow link from a DA 80+ relevant site outperforms 100 links from DA 20 directories. 94% of professional link builders agree.</p>
<p><img loading="lazy" alt="Do-follow backlink statistics showing SEO impact and ranking correlations" src="/images/blog/dofollow-backlink-stats.webp" /></p>
<h2>Do-Follow Backlink Type Priority</h2>
<p>Not all dofollow backlinks carry equal weight. Here is how each type ranks by SEO value.</p>
<p><img loading="lazy" alt="Dofollow backlink types ranked by SEO value from editorial links to wiki links" src="/images/blog/dofollow-backlink-type-priority.webp" /></p>
<p><strong>Editorial and guest post links</strong> carry the most weight. A contextual link within a relevant article on a high-DA site is the gold standard of link building.</p>
<p><strong>.EDU and .GOV links</strong> signal institutional trust. These domains carry inherent authority that search engines respect.</p>
<p><strong>Profile creation links</strong> are the easiest to build. Lower individual impact, but they establish your backlink foundation and diversify your link profile.</p>
<p><strong>Forum and Q&amp;A links</strong> pass authority when you contribute genuine value. Spam posts get deleted.</p>
<p><strong>Web 2.0 and social bookmarks</strong> provide supplementary signals. They work best as part of a diverse <a href="/blog/link-building-strategies/">link building strategy</a>.</p>
